{{bilateral|Egyptian-Swiss|Egypt|Switzerland}}

'''Egyptian-Swiss relations''' are the [[bilateral relations]] <!-- not interstate --> between [[Egypt]] and [[Switzerland]].  Official diplomatic relation between both countries date back from 1909, with the opening of a Swiss trade mission in Egypt.  Egypt has an embassy in [[Berne]] and a general consulate in [[Geneva]].  Switzerland has an embassy in [[Cairo]].

== Luxor massacre ==
{{main|Luxor massacre}}
On November 17, 1997 36 Swiss tourists were killed in [[Luxor]], [[Egypt]], during the Luxor massacre. The attack was perpetrated by [[Al-Gama'a al-Islamiyya]].

