'''Fort Leclerc''' is a military fort at the town of [[Sebha]], [[Libya]].

The fort was originally built by the Italians. It came under control of the [[French Foreign Legion]] during [[World War Two]] when General Leclerc and Free French Forces invaded Italian Libya in 1943. In June 1949 the fort was attacked by local rebels.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://foreignlegion.info/units/3rd-legion-saharan-motorized-company/|title=3rd Legion Saharan Motorized Company|website=Foreign Legion Info}}</ref>
