'''Głuchów Górny''' {{IPAc-pl|'|g|ł|u|h|u|f|-|'|g|u|r|n|y}} ({{lang-de|Ober-Glauche}}) is a village in the administrative district of [[Gmina Trzebnica]], within [[Trzebnica County]], [[Lower Silesian Voivodeship]], in south-western Poland.<ref name="TERYT">{{cite web|url=http://www.stat.gov.pl/broker/access/prefile/listPreFiles.jspa|title=Central Statistical Office (GUS) - TERYT (National Register of Territorial Land Apportionment Journal)|date=2008-06-01|language=Polish}}</ref> Prior to 1945 it was in [[Germany]].

