{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2011}} {{Infobox LGBT rights | location_header = Djibouti {{flagicon|DJI}} | image = LocationDjibouti.png | caption = [[Djibouti]] | legal_status = Legal<ref name="ILGA 2013">{{cite web|url=http://old.ilga.org/Statehomophobia/ILGA_State_Sponsored_Homophobia_2013.pdf |title=State-sponsored Homophobia: A world survey of laws prohibiting same sex activity between consenting adults |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6IEmVxpKn?url=http://old.ilga.org/Statehomophobia/ILGA_State_Sponsored_Homophobia_2013.pdf |archivedate=19 July 2013 |df= }}</ref> | gender_identity_expression = | recognition_of_relationships = No<ref name="ILGA 2013"/> | adoption = No<ref>{{fr icon}} [http://www.diplomatie.gouv.fr/fr/enjeux-internationaux/adoption-internationale-2605/comment-adopter-a-l-etranger/les-fiches-pays/fiches-pays-adoption/article/djibouti Djibouti]</ref> | military = No | discrimination_protections = No<ref name="D">{{cite web|url=http://paei.state.gov/documents/organization/160118.pdf|title=DJIBOUTI|publisher=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514180952/http://paei.state.gov/documents/organization/160118.pdf|archivedate=14 May 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> }}
'''Lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender (LGBT)''' persons in '''[[Djibouti]]''' face legal challenges not experienced by non-[[LGBT]] residents.
==Laws regarding same-sex sexual activity== Same-sex sexual activity is legal in [[Djibouti]].<ref name="ILGA 2013"/>
==Living conditions== The [[U.S. Department of State]]'s 2015 Human Rights Report found that "there were no known reports of societal violence or discrimination based on sexual orientation. Societal norms did not allow for the public discussion of homosexuality, and persons did not openly acknowledge having a homosexual orientation."<ref>[https://www.state.gov/documents/organization/252887.pdf DJIBOUTI 2015 Human Rights Report]</ref>
